[[include :scp-wiki:theme:black-highlighter-theme]]
[[include :scp-wiki:component:toggle-sidebar-bhl]]
[[include :scp-wiki:theme:cyberpunk theme-number=1]]

[[module css]]
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Courier+Prime&display=swap');
@import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=JetBrains+Mono&display=swap');

#page-title {
  display: none;
}

#header h1 a {
  background-image: url(https://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/paradise-lot/pl-logo.png);
}

 #extra-div-1 {
   background-image: url(https://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/paradise-lot/background-pl.png);
   background-size: calc(var(--header-height-on-desktop) * 25);
}

body {
   background-color: rgb(10, 10, 15);
   color: rgb(242, 241, 235);
}

h4 {
   font-size: 1.15em;
   font-family: 'Courier Prime';
   text-align: left;
   text-decoration: underline;
   padding: 0px;
   margin-bottom: 0px;
}

h5 {
   font-size: 1em;
   font-family: 'Courier Prime';
   margin: auto;
   text-align: center;
}

h6 {
   font-size: 1em;
   font-family: 'Courier Prime';
   margin: auto;
   color: rgba(0, 0, 0, 0);
}

.fadein {
   font-size: 1.2em;
   font-family: 'Courier Prime';
   text-align: left;
   font-weight: bold;

   padding-bottom: 0.4em;
   margin-bottom: 0px;
}

hr {
   background-color: rgb(122, 10, 10);
   border-top: .0625rem solid rgb(122, 10, 10);
}

.widebox {
   width: 50vw;
   max-width: 50vw !important;
   position: relative;
   left: calc(-25vw + 50%);
}

@media screen and (max-width: 640px) {
  .widebox {
    width: 100vw;
    max-width: 100vw !important;
    left: calc(-50vw + 50%);
  }

   #header h1 a {
      background-size: auto calc(var(--header-height-on-desktop) - 4rem);
      background-position: center center;
   }
}

.script {
   font-family: 'Courier Prime', monospace;

   padding: 10px 10px 10px 10px;
   margin-bottom: 10px;
   background: repeat-y center/100% url("https://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/paradise-lot/paper-tile-tst.png");
   color: #f2f1eb;

   border: 2px solid #00004d;
}

.start {
   border-bottom: 1px dotted #0f0f38;
}

.middle {
   margin-top: 10px;
   border-top: 1px dotted #0f0f38;
   border-bottom: 1px dotted #0f0f38;
}

.end {
   border-top: 1px dotted #0f0f38;
}

.dialogue {
   padding-left: 30%;
   padding-right: 30%;
   text-align: left;
}

.para {
   text-align: center;
   padding: 0% 35% 0% 35%;
   font-size: 0.8em;
}

.dialogue > p {
   margin-top: 0px;
}

.readout {
   border: none;
   background: repeat-y top/100% url("https://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/paradise-lot/ticker-long.png");

   text-align: left;
   font-family: 'JetBrains Mono', monospace;
   color: #140b00;

   padding: 20px;
   padding-left: 8%;
   margin-bottom: 10px;
}

[[/module]]
[[=image https://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/paradise-lot/1999.png style="width:32%;"]]
++++++ o
[[div class="script start"]]
[[span class="fadein"]]FADE IN:[[/span]]
++++ INT. NEO-HASKELL GENETIC RESEARCH FACILITY/LAB 4Y - NIGHT
It's cold and dark and empty at the facility; the sole exception is Lab 4Y. Machines whirr as the room is illuminated by a single, dismal, blue lamp.

Click. Click. A miniscule piece of amber crystal is placed into a circular holder by a robotic appendage. Lowers down.

A figure stands on the other side of a tempered glass window watching the experiment unfold. 

The crystal is struck by a laser, pulsates, then violently explodes. 

Shades of orange and red bathe the lab and dance off of the figure's glasses.

They smile.
[[/div]]
++++++ o
[[div class="widebox"]]
-----
[[image https://scp-wiki.wdfiles.com/local--files/paradise-lot/anime-ep-alternate.png style="width:100%;"]]
-----
[[/div]]
@@ @@
[[div class="readout"]]
[[>]]
+++ SHIP ONBOARD READINGS\CLASS-04 REGISTERED\//PARADISE//\OUTPUT.
[[/>]]
-----
╠═ **SYSTEM READOUT... PRINTING:**
║░╠ ALL MAJOR INPUTS
║░╚ ALL MAJOR NOTIFICATIONS
║
╠═ **ACTIVATING ALARM [SLEEP CYCLE]... ... [SLEEP CYCLE] ACTIVATED.**
║░╠ ALARM ACTIVATED.
║░╠ ALARM ACTIVATED.
║░╠ ALARM ACTIVATED.
║░╚ ALARM ACTIVATED.
║
╠═ **RECIEVING VOICE COMMAND:**
║░╠ "...just give me TEN more MINUTES."
║░╠ CMND: DELAY ALARM BY __TEN MINUTES__.
║░╚ DELAYING ALARM.
║
║ [...]
║
╠═ **WARNING! INCOMING AUDIO CALL!**
║░╠ AUDIO CALL ROUTED TO: unit.02 (personal quarters)
║░╠ FROM: [ K ]
║░╠ CALL RINGING!
║░╠ CALL RINGING!
║░╠ **LISTENING TO ACTIVE VOICE:**
║░░╠ "SHIP, i thought i said TEN MINUTES, not TEN SECONDS, [expletive]"
║░░╠ INTERPRETING... 
║░░╠ EXTRANEOUS COMMANDS REMOVED.
║░░╠ CMND: DELAY ALARM BY __TEN SECONDS__.
║░░╚ DELAYING ALARM. CONTINUING PROCESS...
║░╠ CALL RINGING!
║░╠ **LISTENING TO ACTIVE VOICE:**
║░░╠ "that's a CALL, isn't it? ugh... can never get sleep..."
║░░╠ INTERPRETING... 
║░░╠ CMND: ANSWER __CALL__.
║░░╚ ANSWERING CALL.
║░╠ **LISTENING TO ACTIVE VOICE:**
║░░╠ "wait, SHIP you didn't ANSWER that call, right? SHIP?"
[[/div]]
@@ @@
[[div class="script middle"]]
++++ EXT. UNCHARTED SECTOR OF THE HAIDURK GALAXY - SPACE
[[size 115%]]**SUPER:** HAIDURK SYSTEM, 1999[[/size]]

Stars dot the emptiness of the void; the only relief is a spaceship the size of a large yacht drifting aimlessly. Its black exterior makes it blend into its surroundings, making obvious the red embossed letters on the side reading 'PARADISE'.

++++ INT. STARSHIP PARADISE/LIVING QUARTERS - SPACE

The room is, to put it bluntly, a real mess. Various effects and tchotchkes are strewn around the quarters, a four-person space haphazardly redressed as a miniature living space. There's only one chair; a malleable ugly amorphous blob of a beanbag. A cracked full-body mirror hangs on to the wall via duct tape. 

By a large port window on the far side of the room lays a bed— on top of that bed lies EKATERINA LOT: a slightly stocky yet lithe woman in her mid twenties. Her carnelian-colored hair is ruffled, barely resembling her usual long inverted bob.

She rubs her eyes before attempting to de-wrinkle her oversized tank top and ill-fitting pants. The voice of K, Lot's work contact, emanates from a phone-like panel nearby the beanbag.
[[div class="dialogue"]]
+++++ K (V. O.)
Yo, Lot, you there?
[[/div]]
She stands up and heads for the phone.
++++++ o
[[div class="dialogue"]]
+++++ LOT
[[span class="para"]](muttering)[[/span]]
Could've called me later...
[[/div]]
Lot passes by the mirror. She does a double-take and tilts her head down to look at her hair. 

Frowns. Continues for the phone.
[[/div]]
@@ @@
[[div class="logs"]]
[[div class="logs-header"]]
[[size 150%]]
AUDIO LOG unit.02
[[/size]]
**> RECORDING STARTED <**
@@ @@
[[/div]]
[[table class="dialog"]]

[[row]]
[[hcell]]
LOT
[[/hcell]]
[[cell class="active"]]
Lot here. What do you want from me so... //early//, K?
[[/cell]]
[[/row]]

[[row]]
[[hcell]]
K
[[/hcell]]
[[cell class="active"]]
It's nearly midday!
[[/cell]]
[[/row]]

[[row]]
[[hcell]]
LOT
[[/hcell]]
[[cell class="active"]]
You mean nearly midday on whatever backwater resort planet you're on.
[[/cell]]
[[/row]]

[[row]]
[[hcell]]
K
[[/hcell]]
[[cell class="active"]]
I'll have you know I'm on Mars.
[[/cell]]
[[/row]]

[[row]]
[[hcell]]
LOT
[[/hcell]]
[[cell class="active"]]
Oh, my point exactly.
[[/cell]]
[[/row]]

[[row]]
[[hcell]]
K
[[/hcell]]
[[cell class="active"]]
Want to keep comparing sizes? I can give the contract to somebody else...
[[/cell]]
[[/row]]

[[row]]
[[hcell]]
LOT
[[/hcell]]
[[cell class="active"]]
Don't let me stop you now.
[[/cell]]
[[/row]]

[[row]]
[[hcell]]
K
[[/hcell]]
[[cell class="active"]]
##41869b|{sighing}## I never get anywhere with you.
[[/cell]]
[[/row]]

[[row]]
[[hcell]]
LOT
[[/hcell]]
[[cell class="active"]]
And yet you still crawl back with more contracts! I'm sure you're making a killing off of me.
[[/cell]]
[[/row]]

[[row]]
[[hcell]]
K
[[/hcell]]
[[cell class="active"]]
Sure am. Anyways, it's another weeklong one, but you never seem to have problems with those. This one's easy to boot - basically a glorified courier job. 
[[/cell]]
[[/row]]

[[/table]]
[[/div]]
